## React Native Expo App

This is a sample React Native app built with Expo.

### Prerequisites

Before getting started, make sure you have the following installed on your machine:

- Node.js
- Yarn
- Expo CLI

### Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/react-native-expo-app.git
   ```

2. Navigate to the project directory:

   ```bash
   cd react-native-expo-app
   ```

3. Install the dependencies:

   ```bash
   yarn install
   ```

### Running the App

To run the app, follow these steps:

1. Start the Expo development server:

   ```bash
   yarn start
   ```

   This will start the development server and provide you with a QR code.

2. Install the Expo Go app on your mobile device from the [App Store](https://apps.apple.com/us/app/expo-go/id982107779) or [Google Play](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=host.exp.exponent&hl=en_US).

3. Scan the QR code displayed in the terminal using the Expo Go app.

   Alternatively, you can open the Expo Go app and use the "Scan QR Code" option to scan the QR code.

4. The app will now be launched on your mobile device.

### Additional Scripts

In the project directory, you can run the following commands:

- `yarn start`: Starts the development server and opens the Expo developer tools in your browser.
- `yarn android`: Builds the app for Android and opens it on an Android device or emulator.
- `yarn ios`: Builds the app for iOS and opens it on the iOS Simulator if you're on a Mac.
- `yarn test`: Runs the test suite for the app.

